class Solution {
public:
    int minBitFlips(int start, int goal) {
        int xorResult = start ^ goal;
        int count = 0;
        while (xorResult) {
            count += xorResult & 1;
            xorResult >>= 1;
        }
        return count;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(max(start, goal)))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution uses bitwise XOR to find the bits that differ between start and goal, then counts the number of 1s in the result, which represents the minimum number of bit flips required.

